The paper deals with fault-tolerant distributed optimization, which involves multiple agents working together to optimize a global cost function. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The optimization problem involves convex cost functions, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The fault-tolerant aspect of the problem involves dealing with crashes and Byzantine faults, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MA, and cs.AI, in that order.
